I'm using Git to manage my two computers and my development. I'm trying to commit changes to GitHub, and I got this error:我正在使用 Git 来管理我的两台计算机和我的开发。我正在尝试将更改提交到 GitHub，但出现此错误：

Failed to push some refs to <repo>. To prevent you from losing history, non-fast-forward updates were rejected. Merge remote changes before pushing again.无法将某些引用推送到 <repo>。为了防止您丢失历史记录，拒绝了非快进更新。在再次推送之前合并远程更改。

What could be causing this, and how can I fix this?是什么原因造成的，我该如何解决？

*branch master->master (non-fast-forward) Already-up-to-date*branch master->master（非快进）已经是最新的

GitHub has a nice section called "Dealing with “non-fast-forward” errors"GitHub 有一个很好的部分叫做“处理“非快进”错误”

This error can be a bit overwhelming at first, do not fear.起初这个错误可能有点让人不知所措，不要害怕。
Simply put, git cannot make the change on the remote without losing commits, so it refuses the push简而言之，git 无法在不丢失提交的情况下在远程进行更改，因此它拒绝推送.
Usually this is caused by another user pushing to the same branch. You can remedy this by fetching and merging the remote branch, or using pull to perform both at once.通常这是由另一个用户推送到同一分支引起的。您可以通过获取和合并远程分支或使用 pull 同时执行这两项操作来解决此问题。

In other cases this error is a result of destructive changes made locally by using commands like git commit --amend or git rebase.在其他情况下，此错误是使用 git commit --amend 或 git rebase 等命令在本地进行破坏性更改的结果。
While you can override the remote by adding --force to the push command, you should only do so if you are absolutely certain this is what you want to do.虽然您可以通过将 --force 添加到 push 命令来覆盖远程，但只有在您完全确定这是您想要执行的操作时才应该这样做。
Force-pushes can cause issues for other users that have fetched the remote branch, and is considered bad practice. When in doubt, don’t force-push.Force-pushes 可能会给已经获取远程分支的其他用户带来问题，并且被认为是不好的做法。如有疑问，请不要强行推动。

Git cannot make changes on the remote like a fast-forward merge, which a Visual Git Reference illustrates like:Git 无法像快进合并那样对远程进行更改，Visual Git 参考说明如下：

This is not exactly your case, but helps to see what "fast-forward" is (where the HEAD of a branch is simply moved to a new more recent commit).这不完全是你的情况，但有助于了解什么是“快进”（分支的 HEAD 只是移动到新的更新的提交）。

The "branch master->master (non-fast-forward) Already-up-to-date" is usually for local branches which don't track their remote counter-part.“branch master->master (non-fast-forward) Already-up-to-date”通常用于不跟踪其远程对应部分的本地分支。
See for instance this SO question "git pull says up-to-date but git push rejects non-fast forward".例如，参见这个 SO 问题“git pull 说是最新的，但 git push 拒绝非快进”。
Or the two branches are connected, but in disagreement with their respective history:或者这两个分支是相连的，但与它们各自的历史不一致：
See "Never-ending GIT story - what am I doing wrong here?"请参阅“永无止境的 GIT 故事 - 我在这里做错了什么？”

This means that your subversion branch and your remote git master branch do not agree on something.这意味着你的 subversion 分支和你的远程 git master 分支在某些事情上不一致。
Some change was pushed/committed to one that is not in the other.一些更改被推送/提交给一个不在另一个中的更改。
Fire up gitk --all, and it should give you a clue as to what went wrong - look for "forks" in the history.启动 gitk --all，它应该会给你一个线索，告诉你哪里出了问题——在历史中寻找“forks”。

It means that there have been other commits pushed to the remote repository that differ from your commits. You can usually solve this with a 这意味着已经有其他提交推送到与您的提交不同的远程存储库。你通常可以用一个来解决这个问题

git pull

before you push在你推动之前

Ultimately, "fast-forward" means that the commits can be applied directly on top of the working tree without requiring a merge.最终，“快进”意味着提交可以直接应用于工作树的顶部而无需合并。

A fast-forward update is where the only changes one one side are after the most recent commit on the other side, so there doesn't need to be any merging. This is saying that you need to merge your changes before you can push.快进更新是一侧的唯一更改是在另一侧最近提交之后，因此不需要进行任何合并。这就是说您需要在推送之前合并您的更改。

Never do a git -f to do push as it can result in later disastrous consequences.永远不要做 git -f 做推送，因为它可能会导致以后的灾难性后果。

You just need to do a git pull of your local branch.你只需要对你的本地分支做一个 git pull。

Ex:前任：

git pull origin 'your_local_branch'

and then do a git push然后做一个 git push

This could also happen if your remote branch is updated and it's not synchronized with your local repo. so in my case, I created a git repo and added readme file. In my local machine, I created new files to upload in that repo, so I tried to push as I normally would do. After that, I did execute $git pull but it threw me fatal: refusing to merge unrelated histories error (comes as normal text in bash). I tried rebasing, re-staging, and re-committing but still, the issue was not solved. In this case, my goal was to merge it anyways since I wanted to keep both and I was not having any common file between them. So, I allowed unrelated history by passing parameter as follows:如果您的远程分支已更新并且未与本地存储库同步，也可能会发生这种情况。所以就我而言，我创建了一个 git repo 并添加了自述文件。在我的本地机器上，我创建了要上传到该存储库的新文件，因此我尝试像往常一样推送。在那之后，我确实执行了 $git pull 但它让我致命：拒绝合并不相关的历史错误（在 bash 中作为普通文本出现）。我尝试了变基、重新登台和重新提交，但问题仍然没有解决。在这种情况下，我的目标是无论如何都要合并它，因为我想保留两者并且它们之间没有任何公共文件。因此，我通过如下传递参数来允许不相关的历史记录：

$git pull origin main --allow-unrelated-histories$git pull origin main --allow-unrelated-histories

This command will merge - ignoring the fact that both were at different heads.此命令将合并 - 忽略两者处于不同头部的事实。

Then push it to the origin branch using: $git push -u origin main然后使用以下命令将其推送到 origin 分支：$git push -u origin main

If anyone is better at explaining this, feel free to edit this answer.如果有人更擅长解释这一点，请随时编辑此答案。

In my case for exact same error, I was also not the only developer.对于完全相同的错误，我也不是唯一的开发人员。

So I went to commit & push my changes at same time, seen at bottom of the Commit dialog popup:所以我去提交并同时推送我的更改，在提交对话框弹出窗口的底部看到：

...but I made the huge mistake of forgetting to hit the Fetch button to see if I have latest, which I did not....但我犯了一个巨大的错误，忘记点击“获取”按钮来查看我是否有最新的，但我没有。

The commit successfully executed, however not the push, but instead gives the same mentioned error; ...even though other developers didn't alter same files as me, I cannot pull latest as same error is presented.提交成功执行，但不是推送，而是给出了同样提到的错误； ...即使其他开发人员没有更改与我相同的文件，我也无法提取最新的文件，因为出现了同样的错误。

The GUI SolutionGUI 解决方案

Most of the time I prefer sticking with Sourcetree's GUI (Graphical User Interface). This solution might not be ideal, however this is what got things going again for me without worrying that I may lose my changes or compromise more recent updates from other developers.大多数时候我更喜欢坚持使用 Sourcetree 的 GUI（图形用户界面）。这个解决方案可能并不理想，但是这对我来说是让事情重新开始的原因，而不用担心我可能会丢失我的更改或危及其他开发人员的最新更新。

STEP 1步骤1

Right-click on the commit right before yours to undo your locally committed changes and select Reset current branch to this commit like so:右键单击您之前的提交以撤消本地提交的更改，然后选择 Reset current branch to this commit，如下所示：

STEP 2第2步

Once all the loading spinners disappear and Sourcetree is done loading the previous commit, at the top-left of window, click on Pull button...一旦所有加载微调器消失并且 Sourcetree 完成加载上一个提交，在窗口的左上角，单击 Pull 按钮...

...then a dialog popup will appear, and click the OK button at bottom-right:...然后将出现一个对话框弹出窗口，然后单击右下角的“确定”按钮：

STEP 3第 3 步

After pulling latest, if you do not get any errors, skip to STEP 4 (next step below). Otherwise if you discover any merge conflicts at this point, like I did with my Web.config file:最新拉取后，如果您没有收到任何错误，请跳至第 4 步（下面的下一步）。否则，如果您此时发现任何合并冲突，就像我对我的 Web.config 文件所做的那样：

...then click on the Stash button at the top, a dialog popup will appear and you will need to write a Descriptive-name-of-your-changes, then click the OK button:...然后单击顶部的 Stash 按钮，将出现一个对话框弹出窗口，您需要编写一个 Descriptive-name-of-your-changes，然后单击 OK 按钮：

...once Sourcetree is done stashing your altered file(s), repeat actions in STEP 2 (previous step above), and then your local files will have latest changes. Now your changes can be reapplied by opening your STASHES seen at bottom of Sourcetree left column, use the arrow to expand your stashes, then right-click to choose Apply Stash 'Descriptive-name-of-your-changes', and after select OK button in dialog popup that appears:...一旦 Sourcetree 完成存储您更改的文件，重复步骤 2 中的操作（上面的上一步），然后您的本地文件将有最新的更改。现在，您可以通过打开 Sourcetree 左栏底部的 STASHES 来重新应用您的更改，使用箭头展开您的存储，然后右键单击以选择 Apply Stash 'Descriptive-name-of-your-changes'，然后选择 OK出现的对话框弹出窗口中的按钮：

IF you have any Merge Conflict(s) right now, go to your preferred text-editor, like Visual Studio Code, and in the affected files select the Accept Incoming Change link, then save:如果您现在有任何合并冲突，请转到您首选的文本编辑器，如 Visual Studio Code，并在受影响的文件中选择接受传入更改链接，然后保存：

Then back to Sourcetree, click on the Commit button at top:然后回到 Sourcetree，点击顶部的 Commit 按钮：

then right-click on the conflicted file(s), and under Resolve Conflicts select the Mark Resolved option:然后右键单击冲突的文件，并在“解决冲突”下选择“标记为已解决”选项：

STEP 4步骤4

Finally!!! We are now able to commit our file(s), also checkmark the Push changes immediately to origin option before clicking the Commit button:最后！！！我们现在可以提交我们的文件了，在点击提交按钮之前勾选立即将更改推送到源选项：

P.S. while writing this, a commit was submitted by another developer right before I got to commit, so had to pretty much repeat steps.附言在写这篇文章时，另一个开发人员在我提交之前提交了一个提交，所以不得不重复很多步骤。

Referring to my answer here... Git push failed, "Non-fast forward updates were rejected"在这里参考我的回答... Git 推送失败，“非快进更新被拒绝”

The safest way to solve this is using --rebase解决这个问题最安全的方法是使用 --rebase

E.g.例如。

git pull <remote> <branch> --rebase

This may cause conflicts in your local branch, and you will need to fix them manually.这可能会导致本地分支发生冲突，您需要手动修复它们。

Once you resolve all the conflicts, you can push your change with --force-with-lease解决所有冲突后，您可以使用 --force-with-lease 推送您的更改

E.g.例如。

git push <remote> <branch> --force-with-lease

Using this flag, Git checks if the remote version of the branch is the same as the one you rebase, i.e. if someone pushed a new commit while you were rebasing, the push is rejected, and you will be forced to rebase your branch again.使用这个标志，Git 检查分支的远程版本是否与你变基的版本相同，即如果有人在你变基时推送了一个新的提交，推送将被拒绝，你将被迫再次变基你的分支。

It is annoying if you are working on a large project with hundreds of commits every hour, but it is still the best way to solve this problem.如果你正在处理一个每小时有数百次提交的大型项目，这会很烦人，但这仍然是解决这个问题的最佳方法。

AVOID USING --force unless you know exactly what you are doing.避免使用 --force 除非你确切地知道你在做什么。

Using --force is destructive because it unconditionally overwrites the remote repository with whatever you have locally.使用 --force 是破坏性的，因为它会无条件地用您在本地拥有的任何内容覆盖远程存储库。

But with --force-with-lease, ensure you don't overwrite other's work.但是使用--force-with-lease，确保你不会覆盖其他人的工作。

See more info on this post in Atlassian's developer blog.在 Atlassian 的开发人员博客中查看有关这篇文章的更多信息。

You need to merge and resolve the conflicts locally before you push your changes to remote repo/fork. 在将更改推送到远程 repo/fork 之前，您需要在本地合并并解决冲突。

1) pull (fetch and merge) 1）拉（取并合并）

$ git pull remote branch

2) Push the changes2) 推送更改

$ git push remote branch

Still you have a quick choice to push forcibly by using --force option but should be avoided as it may result in changes loss or affect badly on other contributors.您仍然可以快速选择使用 --force 选项强制推送，但应该避免，因为它可能导致更改丢失或对其他贡献者产生严重影响。

When you pulled the branch, did you use the "--track" option (in order to keep you local branch tracking the remote branch). If you did not, it can explain that the "merge" command that does not work.当你拉分支时，你是否使用了“--track”选项（为了让你的本地分支跟踪远程分支）。如果没有，则可以说明“合并”命令不起作用。

You can do the merge manually:您可以手动进行合并：

git fetch
git merge origin/groups

To compare local and remote repos, I suggest you this command (add it in an alias, it is usefull):要比较本地和远程回购，我建议您使用此命令（将其添加到别名中，这很有用）：

git log --graph --oneline --all --decorate

It will print the project history tree, showing the branch labels. So you will see where your branch and the origin branch diverge.它将打印项目历史树，显示分支标签。所以你会看到你的分支和原始分支在哪里分开。

Note: if you want to preserve a linear history, instead of a "merge", you can do a "rebase" of your local branch on the remote before pushing:注意：如果你想保留线性历史，而不是“合并”，你可以在推送之前对远程的本地分支进行“rebase”：

git rebase origin/groups
git push origin groups

This is not an answer to the question asked. I had a different problem with the same error message. 这不是所提问题的答案。对于相同的错误消息，我遇到了不同的问题。

My local branch did not have the remote branch to pull the changes from configured properly [git pull]. This was evident from the o/p of git remote show origin. So, I had to use git pull origin <branch_name> instead of git pull to pull the changes.我的本地分支没有远程分支来从正确配置的 [git pull] 中提取更改。这从 git remote show origin 的 o/p 中可以明显看出。因此，我不得不使用 git pull origin <branch_name> 而不是 git pull 来拉取更改。

The syntax of 'git push' supports both an explicit and a shorthand version. The explicit version git push github master works for you. The shorthand version git push does not.“git push”的语法支持显式和速记版本。显式版本 git push github master 适合你。速记版本 git push 没有。

If you use the shorthand version you do not tell git what remote to use and what local branch shall be pushed to what remote branch. Hence git has to guess what you mean.如果你使用速记版本，你不会告诉 git 使用哪个远程分支以及应该将哪个本地分支推送到哪个远程分支。因此 git 必须猜测你的意思。

You can configure this with the setup of your remote and the push.default config:您可以使用遥控器的设置和 push.default 配置来配置它：

   push.default
       Defines the action git push should take if no refspec is given on
       the command line, no refspec is configured in the remote, and no
       refspec is implied by any of the options given on the command line.
       Possible values are:

       ·    nothing - do not push anything.

       ·    matching - push all matching branches. All branches having the
           same name in both ends are considered to be matching. This is
           the default.

       ·    upstream - push the current branch to its upstream branch.

       ·    tracking - deprecated synonym for upstream.

       ·    current - push the current branch to a branch of the same
           name.

Have a look at git branch -vv to check what branch is tracked by your current branch. Then check git config --get push.default to verify it is doing what you expect.查看 git branch -vv 以检查当前分支跟踪的分支。然后检查 git config --get push.default 以验证它是否按照您的预期进行。

The explanation could be related to the default refspec used for remote "github":解释可能与用于远程“github”的默认 refspec 有关：

+refs/heads/*:refs/remotes/github/*

A simple git push would push:一个简单的 git push 将推送：

  • to the remote associated to master (here "github"), because master is the current branch (according to the git status)到与 master 关联的远程（此处为“github”），因为 master 是当前分支（根据 git 状态）
  • all the other branches (master and add_command branches)所有其他分支（master 和 add_command 分支）

add_command is the one which is not in sync with github remote.add_command 是与 github 远程不同步的命令。

git checkout add_command 
git pull github

Then a git push would work.然后 git push 就可以了。
